Daily menu of an obese child: not breakfast and dinner lit
Over one third of children between the ages of 9 and 13 have overweight problems, where overweight affects 9 per cent of the school population and obesity at 5 per cent.
Obese children come from their majority of families with a lifestyle that is not healthy, according to current research.
Again, we demonstrate the importance of the environment where it grows for healthy development of the person, as well as the models that serve as reference.
On the table, obese children are fed, for example, of at least twice as often as children of families with normal weight.
For dinner, more than 19% of the obese had dinner fried potatoes the day before the analysis, which is linked to the prevention program "Obsity is not a coincidence".
There is no practice in children with overweight families to practice sports, which applies to most of the current families, where only 15% of children responded that their parents, at least once a week, have time for physical exercise.
A survey of 900 children
The survey was conducted at the end of last school year and participated in the same almost 900 basic education children from all of the Czech Republic.
It was already the second edition of the program "The obesity of is not a coincidence", which supports the General Health Insurance Company and the company Unilever.
So far, more than 12,000 children have participated in the project from the 4th to the 8th course.
A good diet and sufficient exercise in the family are determinants, which significantly reduce the number of children with overweight and even obesity.
"Only half of the children surveyed have responded that they have five daily meals according to the regime: breakfast, lunch, food, Wednesday and dinner, which is one of the basic conditions for a healthy diet," one of the survey results.
No breakfast but with humid for dinner
Experts warn that, in healthy development, details are important, which also include, for example, a fixed time for family breakfast.
In the Czech Republic, however, only 23% of school families breakfast at the same time.
In most families, each one cooks alone.
But the worst thing was to find out that in 10% of the homes there was nothing to eat.
The breakfast, however, is the basis for a proper daily diet.
The study shows that in the families of obese children, fried potatoes are consumed much more frequently.
Almost all - regardless of weight - drink daily fresh sweets (70%).
Generally, more than 40 per cent of the children surveyed do sports, but among their parents, this result is reduced to less than half, only 15%.
Make Your Diet
The next phase of the study enabled selected boys (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 colleges) to create their own diets from all possible offers according to their tastes and opinions.
"The food preferences of Czech children aged between the ages of 12 and 15 from the point of view of a healthy diet are very far from ideal."
Among its favorite foods are pasta, meat and sweets
"The popularity of sweets is particularly alarming," the final study report warns.
As main food, the palm is taken away from the paste and the bird’s flesh is closely followed.
Practically, children always reject legume and taste for fish and vegetables is very low.
Change to Healthy Habits
At the same time, the study shows that children are willing to change their eating habits if they receive just information.
"In the control group of the participants in the study, who filled the questionnaire after the end of the prevention program "Obsity is not a coincidence", an important change was made in many cases in favor of the principles of a healthy diet," the results of the study are indicated.
It calls attention, for example, to sweet freshness, where many children would begin to prefer normal and current water.
Children would also choose more frequently in the questionnaire poultry and fish for main food and would restrict the consumption of sweet food and flour derivatives.
