Good liars have the ability to read well to others, making them feel at ease, managing their own emotions and intuitively feeling how others perceive them.
We know from the research that extroverts lie more than the introverts, that men say more "false towards themselves", while women say more lies "oriented towards others" -- usually to protect someone's feelings -- that married people lie less often to their partners than people who are not married (but the lies they usually say tend to be "exormous").
